Vulnerabilities.Title: HTTP/2 Rapid Reset attack
Vulnerabilities.Description: The HTTP/2 protocol allows a denial of service (server resource consumption) because request cancellation can reset many streams quickly.

Vulnerabilities.Title: GnuTLS vulnerability
Vulnerabilities.Description: A flaw was found in GnuTLS where the server side of the TLS 1.3 implementation was not properly checking for the signature algorithms in peer's certificate.

Vulnerabilities.Title: Prototype pollution in qs
Vulnerabilities.Description: Prototype pollution in qs <= 6.10.2 allows unauthenticated attackers to cause a denial of service.
